data.description: A rare opportunity to own a home in the charming Mount Pleasant neighborhood has just become available in Easton, Maryland. This 3 Bedroom, 2 Full Bath Rancher with a carport, sits at the end of the cul-de-sac on a quarter acre (.25).  There is plenty of parking for multiple vehicles especially when having friends and family over for gatherings. Eight years ago, this property was renovated. Updates included both full baths, furnace, stainless steel appliances to name a few.  Also, the roof was replaced 4 years ago. There is a huge deck and sunroom at the rear just waiting for your enjoyment. However, the best part of the rear of the property is that it sits on the Rails to Trails in RTC Park. You can also see the John Ford Park at the rear of the property too. Whether you cycle, run, walk, or invite friends over to play soccer or flag football, you won't have to drive to enjoy those activities. So, whether you grew up in Easton or retiring and looking for a quiet neighborhood that offer some healthy activities, this property might just be the one for you.
